org.jasig.cas.ticket.registry

Class CouchbaseTicketRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jasig.cas.ticket.registry.AbstractTicketRegistry
      • org.jasig.cas.ticket.registry.AbstractDistributedTicketRegistry
        • org.jasig.cas.ticket.registry.encrypt.AbstractCrypticTicketRegistry
          • org.jasig.cas.ticket.registry.CouchbaseTicketRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TicketRegistry, TicketRegistryState

    @Component(value="couchbaseTicketRegistry")
public final class CouchbaseTicketRegistry
extends AbstractCrypticTicketRegistry
implements TicketRegistryState
    A Ticket Registry storage backend which uses the memcached protocol. CouchBase is a multi host NoSQL database with a memcached interface to persistent storage which also is quite usable as a replicated tickage storage engine for multiple front end CAS servers.
    Since:
    4.2.0
